  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nOur shuffle function on PR https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/pull/2667  \r\nfail to pass spec tests from here: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-spec-tests/tree/master/tests/shuffling/core\r\nour current implementation is based on protolambda's version of the spec function:\r\nhttps://github.com/protolambda/eth2-shuffle\r\n\r\nas you can see Proto's tests here https://github.com/protolambda/eth2-shuffle/blob/master/spec/tests.csv\r\nalready third case differ from spec test: \r\n`df3f619804a92fdb4057192dc43dd748ea778adc52bc498ce80524c014b81119\t3\t2:1:0`\r\nspec tests:\r\n`- seed: '0xdf3f619804a92fdb4057192dc43dd748ea778adc52bc498ce80524c014b81119'\r\n  count: 3\r\n  shuffled: [2, 0, 1]`\r\nthe spec said to be on the opposite direction (unshuffle) it might be the reason for the diff\r\n\r\nthis is harmony's java implementation that pass the tests: https://github.com/harmony-dev/beacon-chain-java/blob/develop/consensus/src/main/java/org/ethereum/beacon/consensus/spec/HelperFunction.java#L339\r\nyou can see that the order of rounds is the opposite (unshuffle)\r\n\r\nWill be great to have a new set of eyes on the code and find the reason it doesn't pass the spec tests",
